---
import SectionContainer from "../../components/ui/SectionContainer.astro";
import CTAGroup from "../../components/ui/CTAGroup.astro";
---

<section class="bg-[#04101f] py-20 md:py-24">
  <SectionContainer>
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">
        Why Most Google Ads Appeals Fail — And What Google Actually Looks For
      </h2>

      <p class="mt-5 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/72">
        Most advertisers submit appeals that are emotional, vague, or incomplete.
        Google reviewers are looking for structured explanations supported by policy-aligned evidence.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3 gap-5 md:gap-6">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/8 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">
          Google Suspensions Are Based on Risk Signals
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-[15px] leading-7 text-white/68">
          Google evaluates whether an advertiser presents a potential risk to users.
          That judgement can involve website, verification, payment, and account-history signals.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/8 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">
          Google Expects Structured, Policy-Aligned Appeals
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-[15px] leading-7 text-white/68">
          Appeals need to reference policies, explain corrective actions, and include supporting documentation.
          Emotional explanations alone rarely succeed.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/8 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">
          Repeated Appeals Can Make Recovery More Difficult
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-[15px] leading-7 text-white/68">
          Multiple submissions without fixing the trigger often reduce review quality
          and can push the account toward faster automated rejection.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/8 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">
          Google Reviews More Than Just Ads
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-[15px] leading-7 text-white/68">
          Website content, business verification, payment details, and historical account behaviour
          may all contribute to the suspension decision.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/8 bg-white/[0.03] p-6 md:col-span-2 xl:col-span-1">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">
          Not Every Suspended Account Can Be Recovered
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-[15px] leading-7 text-white/68">
          Some accounts become permanently restricted depending on the trigger and account history.
          A structured review is needed to assess whether reinstatement is realistic.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 md:mt-16 flex justify-center">
      <CTAGroup />
    </div>
  </SectionContainer>
</section>